# Phase 5 Rules — Client Portal and Longitudinal Tracking

## What This Phase Builds

- Client Portal Service: curated, approved-only view for clients
  - Executive overview: overall scores, trends, top findings, financial opportunity
  - Domain scorecards: leasing, vacancy, pricing, retention, etc.
  - Finding detail: evidence-backed issues and recommendations
  - Progress tracking: cross-assessment by domain and recommendation
  - Report library: delivered reports and exports
  - Limited explore: pre-approved filters and comparisons only
- Trend & Trajectory Service: longitudinal analysis infrastructure
  - Trend mart materialization in ClickHouse
  - Score trajectory tracking across assessments
  - Recurring finding detection
  - Recommendation adoption tracking
  - Property trajectory dashboards
  - Chronic unit detection
- Assessment comparison views (before/after across engagements)
- Recommendation tracking as structured objects

## Prerequisites

Phase 4 must be complete: workspace functional (studies, snapshots, reports), report templates operational, at least one full assessment completed through the diagnostic pipeline and report generation.

